he witnesses armed police officers known as civil protection and is greeted by the image of dr. wallace breen who is broadcasting a message on a large screen welcoming the new arrivals to city 1 7.

while moving through apartment buildings, gordon finds himself right in the middle of a civil protection raid, barely escaping with his life, and being rescued from certain death by a young woman named alyx vance.
after meeting kleiner's pet headcrab lamarr, gordon receives the mark v hev suit, the upgraded version of his old hev suit from the black mesa incident.
gordon is continually on the run, being chased by the combine, and the few resistance shelters he finds are quickly raided by civil protection, either being shelled or flooded with manhacks.

gordon acquires his first firearm, the 9 mm pistol, and engages in frequent combat with civil protection forces as well as familiar alien enemies such as barnacles, headcrabs, and zombies closer to the end.
gordon is also introduced to the zero point energy field manipulator, also known as the gravity gun, a physics manipulator that quickly becomes indispensable, and dog, alyx's robotic pet.
grigori gives gordon a shotgun and guides him through the town.
as gordon departs, grigori continues fighting the zombies until disappearing into a blazing fire inside a crypt.

mgalekgolo [ 3 ] ( ophis congregatio, meaning serpent union ), more commonly known as hunters, are a unique gestalt of smaller creatures known as lekgolo, which are orange, worm - like creatures. lekgolo were known to group together and form a mgalekgolo for protection during combat, due to the form's increased strength at the cost of maneuverability. when grouped together, the intelligence of the mgalekgolo colony is increased with every additional lekgolo. mgalekgolo are the strongest and the most resilient species within the covenant's army. [ 5 ] a typical mgalekgolo usually stands between 3. 6 6 metres ( 1 2. 0 ft ) and 3. 9 6 metres ( 1 3. 0 ft ) tall, but crouches to between 2. 4 4 metres ( 8. 0 ft ) and 2. 5 9 metres ( 8. 5 ft ) when in its combat state to protect its unarmored stomach and neck. a mgalekgolo can become larger than even a standard covenant wraith. mgalekgolos fight primarily by using the heavy assault cannons integrated directly into their armor on one arm. on the other arm, they carry an enormous and nearly impervious two - part metal shield that is made from the same material that forms covenant warship hulls and weighs approximately two tons., in the style of zdzisÅ‚aw beksinski

matte painting of Deserted terrain, I would even say wasteland. In the foreground (closest to the viewer) is a small hill, languishing in the shadows. A traveler stands on it and looks out into the distance. And in the distance, already in the sunlight, on the flat surface of the desert, stands a huge (skyscraper-sized) cross, half-sided and slightly beveled to the right (from the viewer) side. The cross itself is made of gold, full of patterns and glowing blue elements. And on the sides and behind it, as well as from the side beams hang huge numerous semblances of tentacles in black, from the cross itself also oozes black liquid. In the background even farther away are also deserted hills and uplands. The cross itself and the area around it is illuminated by bright golden sunlight breaking through the clouds. And in the sky, as if floating, fish, whales, and other marine life are flying, rutkowski

A small shopping island in a mall, like a coffee to go, but it sells soup. Above the island is a large signboard that reads soup of the day: hodgepodge, on the counter are baskets of four kinds of bread, and a small sign that reads eat with bread. Behind the counter is a full, red mustachioed man - something between Carlson and Abeli at the side of the counter is a huge cauldron of soup, it is covered with a lid, the lid makes the soup steaming. Next to the cauldron is a pouring table, with a stack of disposable soup bowls and a stack of disposable spoons, unusually shaped - they look like grasses. There are two people in line for the soup - a student and a salesperson from a communications salon. The red-haired soup seller has just given a portion of sausage and bread to a thin, gray-haired grandmother in a light suit and low-heeled shoes, walking briskly away. Granny smiles and enjoys the aroma of the soup, while the seller looks at her with tenderness.

rocky is about the size of a labrador. his exterior has a rough, rock - like quality to it. his skin color varies from blackish - brown to brown. he has five limbs, similar in appearance to a spider. on each limb, there are three fingers. none of his hands appear to have a finger which functions as a thumb. on the top of his carapace, there is a pentagonal outcropping of the same rock - like material as the rest of his body. this has five slits, which is what rocky uses to breathe. his carapace is 1 8 inches wide at its widest, and about 9 inches thick. he is usually wearing a greenish - brown shirt that goes up to his elbows, with a hole on the top and bottom.

1979 'Geometric-Glamorous', this is the mid 1970s - mid 1980s luxurious materials + geometric forms design aesthetic, sometimes referred to as cocaine decor. Bridges the gap between mid-century modern / 1960s lounge styles and the 1980s Art Deco revival 'Deco-Luxe' style and the 'Contempo-Eclectic' style. Common materials include: glass, mirrored glass, steel, brass, lucite/acrylic, gold, silver, granite, marble, plush carpeting, velvet, leather. Tiered forms, angled surfaces, prismatic effects, simple geometric shapes in various compositions, dramatic and even somewhat disorienting spaces. Usually paired with plush, comfortable furniture.

From the outside this house looks nice and traditional. It has been built with white stones and has mahogany wooden decorations. Small, rectangular windows add to the overall look of the house and have been added to the house in a very symmetric way. The house is equipped with a huge kitchen and two bathrooms, it also has a huge living room, five bedrooms, a roomy dining area, a library and a cozy garage. The building is shaped like an L. The extension extends into a covered patio circling around half the house. The second floor is bigger than the first, which creates several overhanging parts on several sides of the house. This floor has roughly the same style as the floor below. The roof is high and square shaped and is covered with rounded roof tiles. One small chimney pokes out the center of the roof. There are no windows on the roof. The house itself is surrounded by paved ground, with a small pond at one side and various potted plants all around the house.
